Bernard Morrison, Thamsanqa Sangweni and Thabo Matlaba will link up with their new club on their last day of preseason training in Johannesburg on Saturday. JOHANNESBURG - Port Elizabeth based Premier Soccer League club Chippa United have confirmed the signings of Orlando Pirates trio Bernard Morrison, Thamsanqa Sangweni and Thabo Matlaba. The three players will link up with their new club on their last day of preseason training in Johannesburg on Saturday before returning with the team to Port Elizabeth next week. The trio now become the Chilli Boysâ€™ 18th signings ahead of the new season.